text.tspan: Ratio of female to male labor force participation rates, 1900 to 2000
Shown is the female-to-male ratio of labor force participation rates, calculated by dividing the labor force
participation rate among women, by the corresponding rate for men. The labor force participation rate is defined as
the proportion of the population ages 15+ that is economically active.
Source: World Bank, Population (Gapminder, HYDE(2016) & UN (2019))
